title: Manhattan
overview: The life of a divorced television writer dating a teenage girl is further complicated when he falls in love with his best friend's mistress.

title: His Girl Friday
overview: A newspaper editor uses every trick in the book to keep his ace reporter ex-wife from remarrying.

title: La vita è bella
overview: When an open-minded Jewish librarian and his son become victims of the Holocaust, he uses a perfect mixture of will, humor, and imagination to protect his son from the dangers around their camp.

title: The Artist
overview: An egomaniacal film star develops a relationship with a young dancer against the backdrop of Hollywood's silent era.

title: The Graduate
overview: A disillusioned college graduate finds himself torn between his older lover and her daughter.

title: Breakfast at Tiffany's
overview: A young New York socialite becomes interested in a young man who has moved into her apartment building, but her past threatens to get in the way.

title: The Quiet Man
overview: A retired American boxer returns to the village of his birth in Ireland, where he falls for a spirited redhead whose brother is contemptuous of their union.

title: The Apartment
overview: A man tries to rise in his company by letting its executives use his apartment for trysts, but complications and a romance of his own ensue.
Inspired by a true story, a comedy centered on a 27-year-old guy who learns of his cancer diagnosis and his subsequent struggle to beat the disease.

title: Good Bye Lenin!
overview: In 1990, to protect his fragile mother from a fatal shock after a long coma, a young man must keep her from learning that her beloved nation of East Germany as she knew it has disappeared.

title: En man som heter Ove
overview: Ove, an ill-tempered, isolated retiree who spends his days enforcing block association rules and visiting his wife's grave, has finally given up on life just as an unlikely friendship develops with his boisterous new neighbors.

title: City Lights
overview: With the aid of a wealthy erratic tippler, a dewy-eyed tramp who has fallen in love with a sightless flower girl accumulates money to be able to help her medically.

title: Moonrise Kingdom
overview: A pair of young lovers flee their New England town, which causes a local search party to fan out to find them.

title: Rushmore
overview: The extracurricular king of Rushmore Preparatory School is put on academic probation.

title: Dil Chahta Hai
overview: Three inseparable childhood friends are just out of college. Nothing comes between them - until they each fall in love, and their wildly different approaches to relationships creates tension.

title: Jeux d'enfants
overview: As adults, best friends Julien and Sophie continue the odd game they started as children -- a fearless competition to outdo one another with daring and outrageous stunts. While they often act out to relieve one another's pain, their game might be a way to avoid the fact that they are truly meant for one another.

title: (500) Days of Summer
overview: An offbeat romantic comedy about a woman who doesn't believe true love exists, and the young man who falls for her.

title: Yeopgijeogin geunyeo
overview: A young man sees a drunk, cute woman standing too close to the tracks at a metro station in Seoul and pulls her back. She ends up getting him into trouble repeatedly after that, starting on the train.

title: Jab We Met
overview: A depressed wealthy businessman finds his life changing after he meets a spunky and care-free young woman.

title: The Shop Around the Corner
overview: Two employees at a gift shop can barely stand each other, without realizing that they are falling in love through the post as each other's anonymous pen pal.
